18 July 2009 *(Handwritten)*

Plants of the Etowah River Basin of Georgia
Dawson County

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata*
Galax
(Poir.) Brummitt

Dawson Forest Wildlife Management Area, Wildcat Creek Tract, accessed from jeep trail just west of Pleasant Union Church, off of Steve Tate Hwy, 1.9 miles S. of Fausett Lake on State Hwy 136. Survey begins at confluence of Amicalola and Wildcat Cr.

Growing in scattered clumps in campground at confluence of Wildcat Cr. with the Amicalola R. In pine leaf litter, sparse herbaceous layer. Dense canopy cover dominated by *Pinus strobus* and *Tsuga canadensis*, also with *Acer rubrum*, *Liquidambar styraciflua*.

Lisa Kruse 01 - 266b
11 June 2001

IMAGED 2013


*Galax urceolata*
*Pinus strobus*
*Tsuga canadensis*
*Acer rubrum*
*Liquidambar styraciflua*
